</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Venezuelan shares fell sharply in nervous trading as a result of the woes
facing Banco Latino, the nation's second-largest bank. At the close, the
Merinvest composite index was down 2.58 per cent to 101.18 on turnover of
12.46m.
