FT  15 JAN 94 / Capital issues hit record Pounds 35.2bn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Capital-raising issues worth a record Pounds 35.2bn were announced by the UK
corporate sector last year, Bank of England figures show. The total in 1992
was Pounds 17.3bn. Almost Pounds 17bn of ordinary share issues were
announced last year, compared with Pounds 6.5bn in 1992. Financial
institutions announced Pounds 15.8bn of capital-raising issues, higher than
1991 and 1992 combined.
The Bank figures show that, after redemptions, net issues by UK borrowers
last year were Pounds 30bn.
