<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / International Company News: Schwab posts 16% profit rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Charles Schwab, the San Francisco-based discount brokerage house, yesterday
announced a 16 per cent improvement in fourth-quarter profits to Dollars
29m, or 48 cents a share.
The strong final quarter took the firm's full 1993 earnings to a record
Dollars 118m, up from Dollars 81m the year before. Schwab also announced
that it was raising its quarterly cash dividend from 5 cents to 7 cents a
share.
Revenues totalled Dollars 258m for the final quarter and Dollars 965m for
the year, increases of 33 per cent and 29 per cent respectively.
Schwab said its record-breaking year was due to a big increase in customer
assets, which jumped by Dollars 30.2bn over the 12 months to Dollars 95.8bn.
Mr Charles Schwab, chairman, said he was confident the firm would have
strong 1994, and set a target for customer assets to rise by another Dollars
30bn by the end of the year.
He warned, however, that because the first quarter of 1993 had been
exceptionally prosperous, Schwab would have difficulty matching that
performance in the first quarter of this year.
The firm's share price fell Dollars 1 7/8 to Dollars 29 5/8 on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</TEXT>
