</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
L. A. Gear, the US sports shoe maker which last quarter reported its first
profit in three years, yesterday said it expected to return to the red in
the fourth quarter with after-tax losses of Dollars 14m to Dollars 16m on
continuing operations.
The company said strong sales of children's shoes had helped cut losses from
Dollars 79.6m to between Dollars 39.2m and Dollars 41.2m for the year to
last Novem-ber.
But it warned that the industry was suffering from high inventory levels
which would probably cut gross margins.
