FT  14 JAN 94 / UK Company News: NU writ against Tarmac
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR, Construction Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Norwich Union has issued a writ for damages, understood to be for up to
Pounds 80m, against a subsidiary of Tarmac, the construction group, for work
on the Galleries shopping centre in Bristol.
Tarmac, meanwhile, is claiming more than Pounds 2m in unpaid fees and costs
it said it is owed for work on the development.
The construction company said it had not had opportunity to analyse details
of the writ but it was 'satisfied the group had no material liability in
this connection.'
Schal International, Tarmac's construction management subsidiary, worked on
the project until spring 1991 when it was replaced. The claims by Norwich
Union relate to the late opening of the development which is now trading and
mostly let.
The construction group, which has rejected Norwich Union's claims, told
shareholders yesterday that the claims have been reviewed but no agreement
has been reached.
