<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Harmony stake in Leisuretime
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Harmony Property, the former hotel and restaurants group, has harked back
towards its old business by acquiring a stake in Leisuretime Inns, the
unquoted pubs operator.
The company, which last month changed its name from Harmony Leisure, said it
was teaming up with Mr Barry Cox, a joint founder and former operator of the
Hard Rock Cafe, to inject fresh finance into Leisuretime.
Mr John Main, Harmony's chairman and chief executive, said the company had
reached agreement with Mr Cox and Mr Bob Halsey, managing director at
Leisuretime, to acquire a joint holding of 29.9 per cent in the group.
Mr Cox, whose latest restaurant operation is called Fatboy's Diner, would
offer extensive catering expertise to the company, Mr Main added.
