<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Hollas in red after restructure
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIGEL CLARK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A review of activities by the new management team at Hollas Group, the
Manchester-based clothing and textiles group, resulted in pre-tax losses of
Pounds 254,000 for the six months to September 30, against profits of Pounds
255,000, writes Nigel Clark.
The outcome was after exceptional costs of Pounds 705,000, comprising Pounds
208,000 relating to management changes and Pounds 425,000 for losses on and
provision against the values of surplus properties.
Of the property charge Pounds 325,000 was accounted for by the net loss on
the sale of a Manchester property announced yesterday. The total
consideration was Pounds 2.4m, raising net cash of Pounds 1.85m which is
being used to cut borrowings and for working capital.
Mr Julian Lee, who retreated from the corporate scene following the sale of
Bricom, the industrial conglomerate, in 1990, came out of retirement to
become group chief executive in October.
Turnover was Pounds 12.8m, against Pounds 15.9m including Pounds 3.83m from
discontinued activities. Losses per share were 0.5p (earnings 0.3p). The
interim dividend is halved at 0.3p.
</TEXT>
