<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / Observer: Fathom that
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Any offers for a second-hand ship from Greenpeace? Jeffrey Woodhead, of
shipbrokers Derrick Holdings, hopes to get as much as Dollars 800,000 for
the 18-year-old good ship Gondwana, which he says has had only two careful
owners.
They may have been careful; but let's consider under what conditions. Before
Greenpeace, the Gondwana, which has an ice-resistant hull, belonged to the
Swedish coastguard, so it probably saw risky duty chasing Soviet submarines.
As for Greenpeace, its vessels spend a good deal of time engaged in highly
dangerous activities, pursuing whalers and ships dumping toxic waste - that
is when they are not being sunk by the French secret service. Still, think
of the brownie points for political correctness; an anti-communist and
ecologically sound ship.
</TEXT>
