<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / Observer: Cordon vert
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
If, as seems increasingly likely, the 'ring of steel' around the City of
London is made permanent, we know who to blame - Stani Yassukovich, the
former Euromarket star whose current hobby-horse is the City Research
Project.
Yassukovich, former chairman of Merrill Lynch Europe, was explaining how
best to improve the UK sterling money markets yesterday when a hack bowled
him a low ball. Why was the City's cordon still in place?
Yassukovich had no hesitation in admitting that he was a permanent cordon
fan. Apart from the fact that many international banking pals liked the
roadblock idea, it has also done wonders to speed up his own journey to the
City from his home in west London.
</TEXT>
