Sir, Your leader, 'An end to foot-dragging', while accepting that my
argument for a statutory regulator has merit, concludes that we should
ignore it and carry on in the present direction regardless. This cannot be
right.
There is no difference between us over the requirement for effective
regulation or over the necessity for public confidence in the eventual
structure. But those objectives are unlikely to be attained unless we
institute the best form of regulation we can devise. This is not
