<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / People: Rhys and Chapman join WDA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The reshaping of the Welsh Development Agency, after last year's blistering
criticism by the Commons public accounts committee, continues apace. John
Redwood, Welsh secretary, is strengthening the board with two new members,
Garel Rhys and Rhiannon Chapman.
Rhys, who holds the chair in motoring economics at Cardiff, is an expert on
the automotive industry; Redwood describes Rhys' expertise as 'particularly
significant' as the motor industry is now the largest single manufacturing
sector in the Welsh economy. Chapman was until recently director of the
Industrial Society and previously personnel director at the London Stock
Exchange.
They will take up their non-executive posts immediately for a three-year
term under David Rowe-Beddoe, who took over as chairman last July. Roy
Thomas, a partner in the law firm Edward Lewis Bevan Ashford, was recently
appointed as the WDA's secretary and legal director.
One post yet to be filled is that of chief executive to replace Philip Head
who resigned in October in the aftermath of the Commons committee report. He
is continuing at the WDA until his successor is appointed.
</TEXT>
