<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Television takes on a wider
role
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD ROSEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Television pictures as big as a sitting room wall have come nearer reality
with the development of Home Theatre by MGM, writes Richard Rosen.
The system looks like the wide-screen TVs used in hotels, but is designed
for the home. The pixels are magnified to lessen the gaps between them and
thus eliminate the picture fuzziness of present systems. An absolute colour
is given to each pixel rather than the conventional system in which an image
is made up by the eye blending red, green and blue dots. On sale from June,
it will cost less than Dollars 1,000. AEEC (MGM licensee): US, 510 416 1259
</TEXT>
