<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): People-mover on a low-cost
journey
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A unique tram system powered by a rechargeable flywheel has this week been
awarded its UK patent, writes Tim Burt.
JM Parry Associates, the company which developed the system, claims it
offers a low-cost alternative to light rail systems relying on overhead
wires or electrified rails.
Local authorities in a number of UK cities have already conducted tests on
the Parry People Movers, which operate on narrow gauge tracks which fit on
to existing roadways or sidewalks. The tram cars are powered by electricity
supplied through short conductor rails along the track. At each halt, the
flywheel recharges for the next stage of the journey. JM Parry Associates:
UK, 384 69171.
</TEXT>
