FT  14 JAN 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Squeezing in the compact
kitchen
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An Italian company which makes kitchen appliances for the US space shuttle
has turned its attention to the business and domestic market with a compact
unit combining a refrigerator, freezer and microwave.
Taking up only a quarter of a square metre, it is designed mainly for
offices, hospitals and surgeries, hotels, factories and apartments.
Berloni's product, called Kitchoo, needs only one plug and is mobile. Priced
at FFr5,000 (Pounds 574), it was developed after a study by ESSEC, the
French business school. Kitchoo Group: France, 45 488383.
