FT  14 JAN 94 / The Westminister Report: Councillors and officers named
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The eight people named in the auditor's statement, apart from Dame Shirley
Porter and Mr Barry Legg, are:
Mr David Weeks: former leader of Westminster City Council who took over
after Dame Shirley resigned in 1991 and still a councillor. Works as a
marketing executive at the London office of construction company Lovell. He
was said yesterday to be on holiday.
Mr Peter Hartley: council member for 10 years until he resigned in 1988. He
is now consultant at a video shop in Praed Street, Paddington.
Mr Michael Dutt: consultant geriatrician at St Albans City Hospital. He was
a Westminster councillor for four years until 1990. He unsuccessfully
contested Leicester South for the Conservatives at the April 1992 general
election.
Ms Judith Warner: a Westminster councillor for 10 years, she is now chairman
of council's education committee and teaches at a college in Surrey.
Mr Bill Phillips: director of NB Selection, a London recruitment
consultancy, who was managing director at Westminster council from 1989 to
1991.
Mr Robert Lewis: joined the council in 1986 as deputy city solicitor and
left in April 1988 to join Freshfields, the City legal firm where he is now
a partner. He 'strongly rejects preliminary findings of the report and will
be challenging them vigorously'.
Mr Graham England: housing director at the council since 1985.
Mr Paul Hayler: divisional director in housing department at Westminster
since May 1986.
