FT  14 JAN 94 / US attacked over death penalty
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Amnesty International accuses the US of executing innocent and mentally ill
people, in a report to be released today, Reuter reports in London.
The death penalty in the US was arbitrary, racist and more expensive than
imprisonment, the human rights group said. It has written to President
Clinton calling for an urgent presidential commission into the death
penalty.
The London-based group said one man on death row in the US was cleared last
year but other innocent people had gone to the electric chair. It criticised
the US for executing people in the last five years for crimes committed when
they were minors.
